{"type":"text","timestamp":1775875028381,"sessionID":"ses_2859a0033ffebouhKNOggdpFNA","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6670d6001iCn4pcZO5lmQL0","messageID":"msg_d7a6661f8001HVI04n5O9WSS7b","sessionID":"ses_2859a0033ffebouhKNOggdpFNA","type":"text","text":"I can see the existing `design.md` and `spec.md` files. Based on the `.sdd_prompt.md` content, I need to update the `design.md` file with additional technical implementation details including architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, and testing strategy. Let me update it:","time":{"start":1775875028379,"end":1775875028379}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875125610,"sessionID":"ses_2859a0033ffebouhKNOggdpFNA","part":{"id":"prt_d7a66759e0012qcD5QzheVHTJp","messageID":"msg_d7a6661f8001HVI04n5O9WSS7b","sessionID":"ses_2859a0033ffebouhKNOggdpFNA","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_54e862f9c7024d7488fd8552","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md","content":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK follows a layered architecture with clear separation between control plane and data plane operations:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Public API Layer                          │\n│  CodeInterpreterClient          AgentRuntimeClient          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n        ┌─────────────────────┴─────────────────────┐\n        │                                           │\n        ▼                                           ▼\n┌───────────────────┐                   ┌───────────────────────┐\n│   Control Plane   │                   │     Data Plane        │\n│  ControlPlane     │                   │  CodeInterpreter      │\n│     Client        │                   │  DataPlaneClient      │\n│                   │                   │                       │\n│  (Session Mgmt)   │                   │  (Code/File Ops)      │\n└───────────────────┘                   └───────────────────────┘\n                                                 │\n                              ┌──────────────────┴──────────────┐\n                              │                                 │\n                              ▼                                 ▼\n                    ┌───────────────────┐           ┌───────────────────┐\n                    │   AgentRuntime    │           │    HTTP Client    │\n                    │  DataPlaneClient  │           │   Utilities       │\n                    │                   │           │                   │\n                    │  (Agent Invoke)   │           │  (Session, Auth)  │\n                    └───────────────────┘           └───────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Responsibilities\n\n| Component | Responsibility |\n|-----------|---------------|\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | High-level facade for code interpretation; orchestrates control plane session lifecycle and data plane operations |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | High-level facade for agent runtime invocations; manages session bootstrapping and payload delivery |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane HTTP client; session creation/deletion via Workload Manager |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client; code execution and file operations via Router |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client; agent invocation via Router |\n| `create_session` | HTTP session factory with connection pooling |\n| `read_token_from_file` | Service account token loading utility |\n| `get_logger` | Structured logging configuration |\n\n### Design Patterns\n\n1. **Facade Pattern**: `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` provide simplified interfaces to complex subsystems\n2. **Context Manager Protocol**: Both high-level clients support `with` statement for automatic resource cleanup\n3. **Dependency Injection**: Lower-level clients are instantiated by higher-level clients with resolved configuration\n4. **Environment Configuration**: Settings resolve from constructor args → environment variables → defaults\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Class Instance Attributes\n\n#### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `name` | `str` | Interpreter session name (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n| `ttl` | `int` | Session time-to-live in seconds (default: `3600`) |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n| `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane client instance |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier (provided or created) |\n| `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client instance |\n\n#### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Target agent runtime name |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Default request timeout in seconds (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout in seconds (default: `5.0`) |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier (bootstrapped or provided) |\n| `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client instance |\n\n#### `ControlPlaneClient`\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `base_url` | `str` | Workload Manager API base URL |\n| `auth_token` | `str` | Bearer token for authentication |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n| `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n\n#### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `session_id` | `str` | Session identifier for header |\n| `base_url` | `str` | Computed Router invocation URL |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n| `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n\n#### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `base_url` | `str` | Computed Router invocation URL |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n| `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n\n### Exception Classes\n\n```\nAgentCubeError (base)\n├── CommandExecutionError\n│   ├── exit_code: int\n│   ├── stderr: str\n│   └── command: Optional[str]\n├── SessionError\n└── DataPlaneError\n```\n\n| Exception | Raised When |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `AgentCubeError` | Base class; not raised directly |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command returns non-zero exit code |\n| `SessionError` | Reserved for session creation/management failures |\n| `DataPlaneError` | Reserved for data plane operation failures |\n\n### Request/Response DTOs\n\n#### Control Plane - Create Session Request\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"string\",\n  \"namespace\": \"string\",\n  \"ttl\": 3600,\n  \"metadata\": {}\n}\n```\n\n#### Control Plane - Create Session Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"string\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Data Plane - Execute Command Request\n\n```json\n{\n  \"command\": [\"string\"] | \"string\",\n  \"timeout\": \"120s\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Data Plane - Execute Command Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stdout\": \"string\",\n  \"stderr\": \"string\",\n  \"exit_code\": 0\n}\n```\n\n#### Data Plane - Write File Request\n\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"string\",\n  \"content\": \"base64-encoded-string\",\n  \"mode\": \"0644\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Data Plane - List Files Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [\"string\"]\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Control Plane API (Workload Manager)\n\n| Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n| Create Session | POST | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `CreateSessionRequest` | `sessionId: str` |\n| Delete Session | DELETE | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | - | `bool` |\n\n#### Create Session\n\n- **URL**: `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n- **Method**: `POST`\n- **Headers**:\n  - `Content-Type: application/json`\n  - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present)\n- **Body**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n    \"namespace\": \"default\",\n    \"ttl\": 3600,\n    \"metadata\": {}\n  }\n  ```\n- **Success Response** (200/201):\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"sessionId\": \"ci-abc123\"\n  }\n  ```\n- **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n\n#### Delete Session\n\n- **URL**: `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n- **Method**: `DELETE`\n- **Headers**: Same as Create Session\n- **Success Response** (200/204): `True`\n- **Not Found** (404): `True` (treated as idempotent success)\n- **Other Errors**: Log and return `False`\n\n### Data Plane API (Code Interpreter via Router)\n\n| Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n| Execute Command | POST | `{base_url}api/execute` | `ExecuteCommandRequest` | `str` (stdout) |\n| Run Code | POST | `{base_url}api/execute` | `ExecuteCommandRequest` | `str` (stdout) |\n| Write File | POST | `{base_url}api/files` | `WriteFileRequest` (JSON) | `None` |\n| Upload File | POST | `{base_url}api/files` | Multipart form | `None` |\n| Download File | GET | `{base_url}api/files/{path}` | - | `bytes` |\n| List Files | GET | `{base_url}api/files` | Query: `path` | `List[str]` |\n\n#### Execute Command\n\n- **URL**: `{base_url}api/execute`\n- **Method**: `POST`\n- **Headers**:\n  - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n  - `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **Body**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"command\": [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hello')\"],\n    \"timeout\": \"120s\"\n  }\n  ```\n- **Success Response** (200): stdout string\n- **Error Response**: Raises `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n- **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout_value + 2.0)` for read side\n\n#### Write File\n\n- **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n- **Method**: `POST`\n- **Headers**:\n  - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n  - `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **Body**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"path\": \"/app/test.py\",\n    \"content\": \"<base64-encoded>\",\n    \"mode\": \"0644\"\n  }\n  ```\n\n#### Upload File (Multipart)\n\n- **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n- **Method**: `POST`\n- **Headers**:\n  - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- **Form Data**:\n  - `file`: binary file content\n  - `path`: remote file path\n  - `mode`: file mode (default: `\"0644\"`)\n\n#### Download File\n\n- **URL**: `{base_url}api/files/{clean_path}` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n- **Method**: `GET`\n- **Headers**:\n  - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- **Query Params**: `stream=True`\n- **Response**: Binary file content\n\n#### List Files\n\n- **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n- **Method**: `GET`\n- **Headers**:\n  - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- **Query Params**: `path` (default: `\".\"`)\n- **Response**: JSON array of file paths\n\n### Data Plane API (Agent Runtime via Router)\n\n| Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n| Bootstrap Session | GET | `{base_url}` | - | `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n| Invoke Agent | POST | `{base_url}` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `requests.Response` |\n\n#### Bootstrap Session ID\n\n- **URL**: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n- **Method**: `GET`\n- **Headers**: None (session default only)\n- **Success Response**: Header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- **Error**: Raises `ValueError` if header missing\n\n#### Invoke Agent\n\n- **URL**: `{base_url}`\n- **Method**: `POST`\n- **Headers**:\n  - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n  - `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **Body**: JSON payload dict\n- **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for all AgentCube SDK errors\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when remote command execution fails\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Reserved for session creation/management failures\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Reserved for data plane operation failures\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n| Component | Error Source | Handling Strategy |\n|-----------|--------------|-------------------|\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `_init_data_plane()` failure | Log warning, delete session, re-raise |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | Context manager exit | Call `stop()` for cleanup regardless of exception |\n| `execute_command` | Non-zero exit code | Raise `CommandExecutionError` |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | 404 on delete | Return `True` (idempotent) |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | Other HTTP errors | Log and return `False` |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | Missing session header | Raise `ValueError` |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | Invoke without session | Raise `ValueError` |\n| HTTP clients | `requests.RequestException` | Propagate to caller |\n\n### Cleanup Guarantees\n\n1. **Context Manager Protocol**: Both `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` implement `__enter__` and `__exit__` for deterministic cleanup\n2. **Stop Method**: `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` ensures:\n   - Data plane session closure\n   - Control plane session deletion (if created internally)\n   - HTTP session close\n3. **Close Method**: `AgentRuntimeClient.close()` ensures HTTP session closure\n4. **Exception Safety**: Cleanup occurs regardless of exception type in `__exit__`\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope | Tools | Location |\n|----------|-------|-------|----------|\n| Unit Tests | Individual classes/methods | `pytest`, `unittest.mock` | `tests/unit/` |\n| Integration Tests | Client-server interaction | `pytest`, test fixtures | `tests/integration/` |\n| End-to-End Tests | Full workflow validation | `pytest`, live environment | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n\n### Unit Test Strategy\n\n#### Mocking Approach\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\nimport pytest\n\n# Example: Mock HTTP session\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_session():\n    session = Mock(spec=requests.Session)\n    session.post.return_value.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-123\"}\n    return session\n\n# Example: Patch create_session\n@patch('agentcube.utils.http.create_session')\ndef test_control_plane_create_session(mock_create_session):\n    mock_session = Mock()\n    mock_session.post.return_value.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-123\"}\n    mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n    \n    client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://test\")\n    session_id = client.create_session()\n    \n    assert session_id == \"test-123\"\n```\n\n#### Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Module | Coverage Target | Key Scenarios |\n|--------|-----------------|---------------|\n| `code_interpreter.py` | 90% | Context manager, session lifecycle, delegation |\n| `agent_runtime.py` | 90% | Bootstrap, invoke, context manager |\n| `control_plane.py` | 95% | HTTP request construction, error handling |\n| `code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | 95% | URL construction, timeout logic, file operations |\n| `agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95% | Session bootstrap, invoke |\n| `utils/` | 100% | Session creation, token reading, logging |\n| `exceptions.py` | 100% | Exception initialization |\n\n### Integration Test Strategy\n\n#### Test Fixtures\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef code_interpreter_client():\n    client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n        router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n        workload_manager_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n        namespace=\"test\"\n    )\n    yield client\n    client.stop()\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef agent_runtime_client():\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n        router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n        namespace=\"test\"\n    )\n    yield client\n    client.close()\n```\n\n#### Integration Test Scenarios\n\n| Test | Steps | Expected Outcome |\n|------|-------|------------------|\n| `test_code_execution` | Create session → Execute `print(\"hello\")` | stdout contains \"hello\" |\n| `test_file_operations` | Write file → List files → Download file | File exists, content matches |\n| `test_agent_invoke` | Bootstrap session → Invoke agent | Valid response from agent |\n\n### End-to-End Test\n\nLocated at `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`:\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"End-to-end test for Code Interpreter with PicoD\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\ndef main():\n    with CodeInterpreterClient(\n        router_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n        namespace=\"default\"\n    ) as client:\n        # Test 1: Simple command\n        result = client.execute_command(\"echo 'hello'\")\n        assert \"hello\" in result\n        \n        # Test 2: Python code\n        result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print(2 + 2)\")\n        assert \"4\" in result\n        \n        # Test 3: File write and read\n        client.write_file(\"test content\", \"/app/test.txt\")\n        result = client.execute_command(\"cat /app/test.txt\")\n        assert \"test content\" in result\n        \n    print(\"All E2E tests passed!\")\n    return 0\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n```\n\n### Continuous Integration\n\n| Pipeline Stage | Tests | Environment |\n|----------------|-------|-------------|\n| Lint | `pytest --flake8`, `mypy` | Isolated |\n| Unit Test | `pytest tests/unit/` | Isolated |\n| Integration Test | `pytest tests/integration/` | Test cluster |\n| E2E Test | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` | Staging environment |\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `requests` | `>=2.28.0` | HTTP client |\n| `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT token handling |\n| `cryptography` | `>=38.0.0` | Cryptographic operations |\n\n### Build Configuration\n\n```toml\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"agentcube-sdk\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\".\"]\ninclude = [\"agentcube*\"]\nnamespaces = false\n```\n\n### Development Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pytest` | Test framework |\n| `pytest-mock` | Mocking utilities |\n| `pytest-cov` | Coverage reporting |\n| `mypy` | Static type checking |\n| `flake8` | Code style linting |\n| `black` | Code formatting |\n\n## Logging Strategy\n\n### Logger Configuration\n\n```python\ndef get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n    logger = logging.getLogger(name)\n    logger.setLevel(level)\n    \n    if not logger.handlers:\n        handler = logging.StreamHandler()\n        formatter = logging.Formatter(\n            '%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s'\n        )\n        handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n        logger.addHandler(handler)\n    \n    return logger\n```\n\n### Log Levels\n\n| Level | Usage |\n|-------|-------|\n| `DEBUG` | HTTP request/response details, configuration resolution |\n| `INFO` | Session creation/deletion, major lifecycle events |\n| `WARNING` | Non-critical errors (404 on delete), fallback behavior |\n| `ERROR` | Operation failures, exceptions |\n\n### Example Log Output\n\n```\n2024-01-15 10:30:00 - agentcube.code_interpreter - INFO - Creating session: my-interpreter\n2024-01-15 10:30:01 - agentcube.control_plane - DEBUG - POST http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter\n2024-01-15 10:30:01 - agentcube.code_interpreter - INFO - Session created: ci-abc123\n2024-01-15 10:30:02 - agentcube.data_plane - DEBUG - POST http://router:8080/.../api/execute\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Authentication\n\n1. **Control Plane**: Bearer token via `Authorization` header\n   - Token from constructor argument `auth_token`\n   - Fallback to service account token file: `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n\n2. **Data Plane**: JWT handled by Router; SDK does not set `Authorization` header\n\n### Session ID Security\n\n- Session ID transmitted in `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- Session ID should be treated as sensitive (grants access to sandbox)\n- Automatic session cleanup on context manager exit\n\n### File Operations\n\n- No local file system access outside provided paths\n- Upload/download operations require explicit local path specification\n- Remote file paths validated/cleaned before use\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775875125496,"end":1775875125606}}}}
